{"word":"ὀμματοστερής","slug":"ὀμματοστερής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀμματοστερής</b></el> <el>(ὀμμᾰτο-στερής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:στερέω'><el>στερέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>bereft of eyes</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>depriving of eyes</i>, <el>φλογμὸς ὀμμ. φυτῶν</el> heat <i>that robs</i> plants <i>of their eyes</i> or <i>buds</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}